                     <note type="paleography">Written along the fibers in black ink with a thick pen; the letters are of large sized cursive; well-formed ornamental hand; typical of the Byzantine period; the letters are characterized by looped eta; phi, iota and rho sometimes invade the interlinear spaces; final sigma is prolonged with a curved lined ended with a hook; the interlinear spaces are almost even of c.a. 1 cm; the text is begins with the Christian sign. Verso is blank.</note>
